3. 養聲
廣東話：佢係個歌手，最近要喺屋企好好養聲，唔好令聲帶受損。
English: He is a singer; recently he needs to rest his voice at home to prevent his vocal cords from getting damaged.

4. 票尾
廣東話：買咗張飛去澳門嘅車票，記得將票尾搣落嚟留返做收據。
English: Bought a ticket to Macau, remember to tear off the stub and keep it as a receipt.

5. hacker
廣東話：個 hacker 企圖入侵銀行系統，但最後被警方捉咗。
English: The hacker tried to hack into the bank system but was eventually caught by the police.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：屋企後園種咗幾株石斛蘭，佢哋好鍾意依附喺樹幹上面生長。
English: We planted a few Dendrobium orchids in the backyard; they love growing by clinging to tree trunks.

7. 吊詭
廣東話：呢個情況真係好吊詭，明明佢話唔知，點解證據全部喺佢度？
English: This situation is really paradoxical; he clearly said he didn't know, yet all the evidence is with him.

8. 吊詭
廣東話：佢成日話自己好勤力，但係成日遲到，真係好吊詭。
English: He always says he's hardworking, but he's always late; it's really absurd.

9. 各為其主
廣東話：雖然佢哋係好朋友，但因為各為其主，最後都變成對手。
English: Although they were good friends, because each served their own master, they eventually became rivals.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：佢個車軨蓋壞咗，要即刻去車房換新嘅。
English: His car hubcap is broken; he needs to go to the garage to get a new one immediately.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：佢老細好鍾意週末去高爾夫球場打哥夫。
English: His boss loves going to the golf course to play golf on weekends.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間餐廳好特別，所有套餐都係免揀，廚師點咩你就食咩。
English: This restaurant is special; all set meals are non-selectable, you eat whatever the chef cooks.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢買咗部新車，成日帶住朋友去擺闊佬，好唔實際。
English: He bought a new car and often takes friends around to show off his wealth; it's very unrealistic.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我成日喺放工路上聽廣播劇，好過癮。
English: I often listen to radio dramas on my way home from work; it's very enjoyable.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：屋企部舊錄影機壞咗，唔知點解唔可以錄電視節目。
English: The old video recorder at home is broken; I don't know why it can't record TV programs anymore.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：佢喺案發現場留下咗個字條，真係吟詩吟唔甩，想抵賴都唔得。
English: He left a note at the crime scene; the evidence is undeniable, he can't deny it no matter what.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：教會下個月會舉行大型佈道大會，邀請咗好多講員。
English: The church will hold a large evangelism conference next month, inviting many speakers.

18. 寫手
廣東話：佢係個專業寫手，專門幫人寫文章同報告。
English: He is a professional writer, specializing in writing articles and reports for others.

19. 寫手
廣東話：呢間公司好需要個寫手，幫佢哋寫廣告文案。
English: This company really needs a ghostwriter to help them write ad copy.

20. 代打
廣東話：我唔識玩呢款遊戲，可以唔可以請人代打？
English: I don't know how to play this game; can I hire someone to play for me?

21. 茶碗
廣東話：佢好鍾意收藏日本嘅茶碗，每隻都好精緻。
English: He loves collecting Japanese tea bowls; each one is very exquisite.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：沖茶嘅時候用個茶隔，就可以將茶葉同茶湯分開。
English: When brewing tea, use a tea strainer to separate the tea leaves from the tea soup.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：公司只許老闆遲到，唔准員工遲到，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The company allows the boss to be late but not the employees; it's truly "only the magistrate can set fires, but commoners are not allowed to light lamps."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：今晚演唱會嘅壓軸節目係佢嘅獨唱。
English: Tonight's concert finale is his solo performance.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢係個快人快事，有咩問題就即刻解決，唔會拖泥帶水。
English: He is a straightforward person; if there's a problem, he solves it immediately without dragging things out.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：成日喺公廁入面見到四腳獸，真係好唔文明。
English: I often see "four-legged beasts" (people having sex) in the public restroom; it's really uncivilized.

27. 無米粥
廣東話：我哋而家只係煲無米粥，等條件成熟先正式簽約。
English: We are just having preliminary talks for now; we'll sign the formal contract once the conditions are ready.

28. 義會
廣東話：以前好多窮人靠義會先可以攞到錢做生意。
English: In the past, many poor people relied on rotating savings associations to get money to do business.

29. 榜文
廣東話：古代嘅皇帝會貼榜文，宣佈重要嘅政策。
English: Ancient emperors would post edicts to announce important policies.

30. MK名
廣東話：佢個網名係個典型嘅 MK 名，加咗好多奇怪嘅符號。
English: His online nickname is a typical MK name, with many strange symbols added. [end of text]


